public TableChanges changesForTable(String tableName,
                                    long version)
                             throws AppGluRestClientException
The returned TableChanges will contain rows if the server version of the table is higher that the local one.

Specified by:
changesForTable in interface SyncOperations
Parameters:
tableName - the name of the table

Returns:

AppGluRestClientException

changesForTables

public List<TableChanges> changesForTables(List<TableVersion> tables)
                                    throws AppGluRestClientException
Return a list of TableChanges, one for each specified TableVersion.
For each TableChanges returned, it will contain rows if the server version of that table is higher that the local one.
Since the response can be very large, to consume less memory, the use of SyncOperations.changesForTables(List, TableChangesCallback) may be more appropriate.

Specified by:
changesForTables in interface SyncOperations
Parameters:
tables - table names and versions
Returns:
a list of TableChanges
Throws:
AppGluRestClientException

Return a list of TableChanges, one for each specified TableVersion.
For each TableChanges returned, it will contain rows if the server version of that table is higher that the local one.
Since the response can be very large, to consume less memory, the use of SyncOperations.changesForTables(TableChangesCallback, TableVersion...) may be more appropriate.

changesForTables

public void changesForTables(TableChangesCallback tableChangesCallback,
                             TableVersion... tables)
                      throws AppGluRestClientException
Returns the same result as SyncOperations.changesForTables(TableVersion...). However, instead of parsing the whole response and return it all together, it will parse one table and one row at a time and send that to the provided TableChangesCallback.
The advantage is that it will consume less memory, but the parsing code is more complex. Since changes can be a very large response, this method is more appropriate.

Specified by:
changesForTables in interface SyncOperations
Parameters:
tableChangesCallback - a callback to receive the tables and rows that were changed
tables - table names and versions
Throws:
AppGluRestClientException
